@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001
@TOKEN = replace-with-admin-jwt
@recipientEmail = your-test-email@example.com

# Recruitment Mail Controller Endpoints
# 1) Login as an admin and paste JWT into @TOKEN
# 2) Replace @recipientEmail with the inbox you want to receive test mail
# 3) Use /send for direct SMTP testing, /batch for DB template testing

### Send direct email immediately (protected)
POST {{baseUrl}}/recruitment/mail/send
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{TOKEN}}

{
  "subject": "[TTS Dev] Test mail from recruitment module",
  "recipients": [
    {
      "email": "{{recipientEmail}}",
      "fullName": "Mail Test Receiver",
      "htmlBody": "<h2>TTS recruitment mail test</h2><p>If you received this email, SMTP is working correctly.</p><p><strong>Sent at:</strong> 2026-03-15 10:00</p>"
    }
  ]
}

### Send template-based email (protected)
# Requires templateCode to exist in the email_templates table first.
POST {{baseUrl}}/recruitment/mail/batch
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{TOKEN}}

{
  "templateCode": "interview_invitation",
  "recipients": [
    {
      "email": "{{recipientEmail}}",
      "fullName": "Nguyen Van A",
      "interviewTime": "08:00 25/02/2025",
      "location": "Van phong Cong ty"
    }
  ]
}
